What I was doing wrong as @Adam pointed out in the comments was not returning anything while making the call in the recursive block. Note, the response from an async function can only be a promise hence, the call to the function was made within a new promise block and resolved/rejected. This sent a proper response instead of an undefined response.The correct code is:

if(retryCount === 1){                   
                    throw err; // important to throw an error here
                }else{
                     return new Promise((resolve, reject) =&gt; {
                        setTimeout(() =&gt; {                            
                            getApiCall(config,flow, retryCount-1).then((response) =&gt; {
                                return resolve(response);
                            }).catch((err) =&gt; {
                                global.logger.info(&#39;Error&#39;+err);
                                return reject(err);
                            })                                                                      
                        }, 1000)
                    }) 
                }

